Git is Version Control System(VCS) OR Source Code Management(SCM) - Git is a DevOps tool used for source code management. 
It is a free and open-source version control system used to handle small to very large projects efficiently. 
Git is used to tracking changes in the source code, enabling multiple developers to work together on non-linear development.
History of git
Source Code Control System(SCCS) - Stored original version and sets of changes | 1972: free with Unix

GIT Installation in Debian/Ubuntu

For the latest stable version for your release of Debian/Ubuntu
# apt-get install git
For Ubuntu, this PPA provides the latest stable upstream Git version
# add-apt-repository ppa:git-core/ppa # apt update; apt install git
 
Configuration 
System - /etc/gitconfig
	  Program Files\Git\etc\gitconfig
User :   ~/gitconfig
$HOME\.gitconfig

Project :- my_project/.git/config

Basic command which always get config
System :- git config --system
User :- git config -- global
Project :- git config

git config --global user.name “Mohammad Imteyaz”
git config --global user.email “email-id”
git config --list = it will list all the configuration

Terminal - 
git config --global user.name
<Mohammad Imteyaz>
imteyaz@imteyaz-HP-630-Notebook-PC:~$ git config --global user.email
<imteyazm745@gmail.com>

git config --global core.editor “atom -wait” 	use to select the editor  
git config --global color.ui true      		gives the color

